news.title: Existing home sales in U.S. drop 5.9% in October 2022
news.para: House resales, which account for a big chunk of U.S. home sales, slumped 28.4% on a year-on-year basis in October. That was the largest drop since February 2008.

news.title: NCLAT stays insolvency proceedings against BPTP
news.para: ​On November 14, the National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT) had directed to initiate insolvency proceedings against BPTP Ltd, a leading real estate player in Delhi-NCR, on a petition filed by an operational creditor, RBCL Projects.

news.title: Delhi: Metropolis Lab's MD buys Sunder Nagar bungalow for Rs 64 crore
news.para: Shah has paid Rs 2.56 crore stamp duty for the registration of the property. According to documents accessed by CRE Matrix, a real estate data analytics firm, Star hotel PVR Ltd has sold the bungalow and property has been registered on October 31.

news.title: Housing societies will need norms for EV charging, says Bombay HC
news.para: The petition contents that the charging time for EVs is between 3 hours and 30 hours and hence it becomes imperative for the owner of such vehicles to have access to charging infrastructure at their residence where they can charge their electric vehicles overnight or during weekends.

news.title: GVMC plans to develop model slum in each zone of Visakhapatnam
news.para: The GVMC will conduct a survey to understand the infrastructural matrix in these slums related to engineering, sewerage, water supply, town planning, sanitation, etc. and address them on a priority basis.

news.title: Two Bengaluru metro phase III corridors get government's in-principle nod
news.para: Phase 3 consists of 44.6km with two corridors: JP Nagar 4th Phase-Kempapura along ORR West (32.1km) and Hosahalli-Kadabagere along Magadi Road (12.5km).

news.title: Navi Mumbai: Cidco told to put bars to stop sand mining in Taloja creek
news.para: State additional chief secretary Nitin Kareer during a review meeting has instructed to hand over all CRZ land to forest department mangrove cell, and place measures to contain illegal sand dredging and destruction of mangroves.

news.title: Owner fails to pay tax, Chandigarh civic body seals property
news.para: Officials said that they asked the owner to pay the tax amount on time but he was reluctant. Therefore, the authority was left with no option but to seal the property on Thursday.

news.title: Gomtinagar & Jankipuram Extension colonies now under Lucknow civic body
news.para: LDA will give around Rs 35 crore to LMC for the work related to infrastructure facility development and garden beautification of areas under Jankipuram Yojana, Sector-J and Jankipuram Extension Yojana, Sector-1 to 11, Vikalp Khand and Viraj Khand.

news.title: NGT asks builder to pay Rs 10 crore for Aravali tree felling
news.para: The National Green Tribunal (NGT) has ordered a private company to pay compensation of Rs 10 crore for illegally felling 500 trees on five acres of protected Aravali land in Faridabad, fixing the rate of compensation at Rs 2 lakh per tree.

news.title: Five mixed-land use plots up for grabs near Noida airport site
news.para: While allottees can develop industry on 75% of the land allotted to them, the remaining plot can be used for setting up residential and commercial structures as well as utilities.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC gives property tax relief to only a handful
news.para: “The government directed us to give relief as people had suffered financial losses owing to Covid, and are yet to recover from it,” said municipal commissioner and now administrator Iqbal Chahal.

news.title: Noida: Install anti-smog guns, register on portal, builders told
news.para: Praveen Kumar, regional officer of UPPCB in Noida, said that the department has started sending notices to developers to ensure C&D rules are met.

news.title: Kolte-Patil Developers, two other settle case with Sebi
news.para: This comes after three applicants proposed to settle the alleged violations of LODR (Listing Obligations and Disclosure Requirements) Regulations "without admitting or denying the findings" through a settlement order.

news.title: Kaisa delays offshore debt revamp talks on uncertain sector outlook: Sources
news.para: The second-largest U.S. dollar bond issuer among Chinese developers after China Evergrande Group, Kaisa has been in the process of restructuring its $12 billion offshore debt after defaulting on some bonds last year.
